The shooting comes ahead of South Sudan's fifth independence day on Saturday.
Celebrations have been cancelled in order to save money.
Mr Machar's spokesman Nyarji Roman said the situation was now calm after the shooting on Thursday night.
"I want to tell the public that there should be no panic - the leadership ordered  the two forces to go back to their barracks," the Agence France-Presse news agency quotes him as saying.
